Almond Croissant Cookies
  --Britney Brown-Chamberlain

Filling:
4 tbsp (56 g) Salted Butter, (room temperature)
6 tbsp (75 g) Sugar
1 1/4 c (140 g) Almond Flour
1 (30 g) Egg White, (save the egg yolk for the cookie dough)
1 tsp Almond Extract

Combine butter and sugar in a bowl. Mix together until combined, then add almond flour, egg white, and almond extract. Continue to mix until smooth and combined, ~1 min. Place into the refrigerator until ready to use.

Cookie Base:
1 c (227 g) Salted Butter, (room temperature)
1 c (200 g) Sugar
1/2 c (110 g) Brown Sugar
1 large (50 g) Egg, (room temperature)
1 (18 g) Egg Yolk
1 tsp (5 g) Vanilla 
1 1/2 tsp (8 g) Almond Extract
2 3/4 c (344 g) ap Flour
1 tsp (4 g) Baking Soda
1/2 tsp Kosher Salt
1/8 tsp Nutmeg
1 c Sliced Almond, (for rolling the cookies)

In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, add butter, sugar, and brown sugar. Mix on medium speed for 3 min, the scrape down the sides of the bowl. Add eggs and egg yolk and mix until combined. Scrape down the sides of the bowl again, then add vanilla and almond extract. Continue to mix until combined. Add in the flour, baking soda, kosher salt, and nutmeg. Mix together until the cookie dough forms and there's no patches of flour, ~30 s. Remove the frangipane filling from the fridge. Use a large cookie scoop (~3 tbsp of cookie dough) and scoop out the cookie dough. Flatten into a disc and scoop out 1 tbsp of the frangipane filling and place in the center of the disc. Roll the dough around the filling, ensuring it's fully tucked in. Place cookies onto a baking sheet and refrigerate for 1 hr. (if refrigerating longer (up to 24 hr), cover with plastic wrap so that the cookies don't dry out) Preheat the oven to 350F. Add sliced almonds into a small bowl. Roll each cookie dough ball in the almonds, pressing them into the cookie. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and cookie about 5-6 cookies onto the cookie sheet, spaced ~3" apart. Bake for 12-14 min, until the edges are set and the centers are puffed. Use a small bowl to swivel around the cookies so that they get that perfect circular shape (optional). Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for 10 minutes, then remove onto a wire rack. Dust with powdered sugar then allow them to cool completely.

